  "texts": [
    "In the analysis of figures (a, b) and (c, d), it is observed that for GPT-3.5, prompts encompassing all domains generally yield improved results in most areas.",
    "Conversely, for GPT-4, domain-specific prompts tend to produce better outcomes.",
    "particularly GPT-3.5, there is a tendency to choose options \"A\"and \"C\"; however, GPT-4 exhibits no clear preference for any option.",
    "Option \"E\" denotes that none of the presented choices are correct; option \"F\" indicates that all options are correct, and option \"G\" signifies instances where the LLMs fail to generate an output that includes an answer.Figure 1:1Figure 1: Distribution of accurate responses to a set of 126 questions crafted for human participants.",
    "(a) The aggregate distribution of accurate answers reveals a predominant selection of options \"B\" and \"C\", with \"A\" being the least chosen, aligning with human intuition."
